## Design Notes

| Area | Decision |
|---|---|
| **HTTP verb** | `PATCH` — partial update semantics; swap for `PUT` if your API mandates full replacement. |
| **Status codes** | `200 OK`, `401`, `403`, `404`, `422 Unprocessable Entity` (RFC 9110 / JSON:API convention). |
| **Mandatory fields** | `title`, `amount`, `currency`, `expense_date`, `category` — adjust to match your domain model. |
| **Audit service** | Mocked via `unittest.mock.patch`; replace `app.services.audit_service.write_audit_record` with your real import path. |
| **Test client** | Uses a `MagicMock` client so the suite runs without a live server. Replace with FastAPI `TestClient`, Flask `test_client`, or `httpx` as appropriate. |
| **Parametrize** | `@pytest.mark.parametrize` is used to cover every mandatory field in a single concise loop. |
